      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "@casey not necessarily. If you know the control port, generally 127.0.0.1:9051, you can send a \"PROTOCOLINFO\" command to find out what auth is expected and what cookie file. Tor Browser Bundle is set up using coookie authentication by default. Though I'd say the user does have at least to give an 'OK' to do this.\n\nOnly in the case of HashedPassword, credentials have to be manually configured.\n\nI have a base implementation based on libevent (from #5677) here: https://github.com/laanwj/bitcoin/blob/2015_08_tor_hs/src/torcontrol.cpp\nIt authenticates and requests the hidden service, ~~but does not actually integrate into bitcoin yet ;)~~\n",
