      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "@laanwj Hmmâ¦ checking the filename might be a little klugey, since I would assume some locally installed malware that's pretending to be Tor could might be capable of doing some workaround, e.g. symlinking `evil_control_auth_cookie` to `wallet.dat`, and then asking you to read it. You could use `SAFECOOKIE` authentication, and then you'd have the guarantee that whatever is listening is also able to read the contents of the cookie file. (The protocol for using `SAFECOOKIE` is described [here](https://gitweb.torproject.org/torspec.git/tree/control-spec.txt?id=09ff9e20#n1211).)\n",
